Add a 1-minute countdown timer to the questions game screen. 

1. First read `components/GameDynamicsScreen.tsx` and any other game/questions related files (search in `app/(tabs)/`, `components/`) to understand the current implementation.

2. Add a countdown timer with these requirements:
   - Starts at 60 seconds (1 minute) when each question is shown
   - Counts down every second (60, 59, 58... 2, 1, 0)
   - Resets to 60 when moving to the next question
   - When it reaches 0, show the "Continuar" / next button (if it was hidden before) or enable it (if it was disabled)
   - While the timer is still running (> 0), the continue button should be hidden or disabled
   - Display the countdown visually on screen (e.g. a circular timer or just a number with "s" suffix)

3. Implementation details:
   - Use `useRef` for the interval to avoid memory leaks
   - Clear the interval with `clearInterval` when component unmounts or question changes
   - Use `useState` for the countdown value
   - Reset the timer in a `useEffect` that depends on the current question index

4. Visual design for the timer:
   - Show the countdown number prominently (large font, e.g. size 28-32)
   - Use a circular progress indicator or just a styled number badge
   - Color: green when > 30s, orange when 10-30s, red when < 10s
   - Position it at the top of the question card or near the question
   - When timer hits 0, show a brief "¡Tiempo!" text and then reveal the continue button

Example timer logic:
```tsx
const [timeLeft, setTimeLeft] = useState(60);
const timerRef = useRef<ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null>(null);

const startTimer = () => {
  if (timerRef.current) clearInterval(timerRef.current);
  setTimeLeft(60);
  timerRef.current = setInterval(() => {
    setTimeLeft(prev => {
      if (prev <= 1) {
        clearInterval(timerRef.current!);
        return 0;
      }
      return prev - 1;
    });
  }, 1000);
};

// Reset timer when question changes
useEffect(() => {
  startTimer();
  return () => {
    if (timerRef.current) clearInterval(timerRef.current);
  };
}, [currentQuestionIndex]);
```

Make sure the continue/next button is only shown/enabled when `timeLeft === 0`.

